  "preFix": {
    "title": "Pea and mint soup",
    "subtitle": "Fresh, bright, and ready in fifteen minutes",
    "excerpt": "Frozen peas blended with mint, a little stock, and a swirl of crème fraîche. One of the quickest soups there is, good hot or cold, and an excellent use for frozen peas.",
    "sourceNotes": "Standard British spring soup, widely published from the 1980s onward. Frozen peas as a year-round substitute for fresh peas became a British domestic staple in the 1960s and has been used in soups ever since.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pea and mint soup is fifteen minutes from start to finish. Frozen peas are already ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "blanched",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "termId": "cmpry6m710000fsv4lwuyz6jc"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " and need very little cooking: a brief simmer in stock, then into the blender with a handful of fresh mint. The key to keeping the colour vivid is speed: overcook the peas and the soup turns khaki.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
