        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and cook for 6 minutes until soft.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{garlic}} of crushed garlic and cook for 1 minute. Pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock and bring to a simmer.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add {{peas-frozen}} of frozen peas straight from the freezer. Return to a simmer and cook for exactly 3 minutes. Do not overcook.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and serve",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Transfer the soup to a jug blender in batches. Add the mint leaves. Blend until completely smooth.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Return to the pan over a low heat. Stir in {{creme-fraiche}} of crème fraîche and the juice of {{lemon}} lemon. Taste and season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Add a small spoonful of crème fraîche to each bowl and a mint leaf on top.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Three minutes for frozen peas is enough. If the soup has gone dull, try adding a handful of fresh raw spinach leaves into the blender with the cooked peas: they boost the colour back.",
                "cause": "The peas were cooked for too long, destroying the chlorophyll.",
                "symptom": "Soup is khaki rather than vivid green"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a brand of frozen peas with a high sugar content (the packaging sometimes states 'garden peas' or 'petits pois'). The freshness of the peas matters for flavour.",
                "cause": "Old or cheap frozen peas with a lot of starch.",
                "symptom": "Soup tastes starchy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a jug blender and blend for at least 60 seconds. Pass the blended soup through a sieve for an extremely smooth result.",
                "cause": "A stick blender does not produce as fine a result as a jug blender for pea soup.",
                "symptom": "Texture is not smooth"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Start with 15 g rather than 20 g. You can always add a little more to the jug and blend again; you can't take it out.",
                "cause": "Too much mint added to the blender.",
                "symptom": "Mint flavour is too strong or medicinal"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Serve cold in summer as a chilled soup starter: make it, chill it for at least two hours, then thin with a little extra stock and serve with a spoonful of crème fraîche. Watercress can replace half the peas for a more peppery version.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pea soup is one of the oldest in the British canon. Elizabethan recipes made it with fresh garden peas. The frozen version is a modern convenience. Frozen peas are picked and frozen within hours, which makes them sweeter and fresher than peas left in the pod for days.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 4,
